               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120219-16-person187">
                  SOPHIA 
                  HALSON
               <interp inst="t18120219-16-person187" type="surname" value="HALSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120219-16-person187" type="given" value="SOPHIA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120219-16-person187" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of 
               <persName id="t18120219-16-person188">
                  Jacob 
                  Halson
               <interp inst="t18120219-16-person188" type="surname" value="Halson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120219-16-person188" type="given" value="Jacob"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120219-16-person188" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I lost these things on the 20th of January, it was half past ten o'clock when I missed them. The prisoner took these clothes when I was talking to a captain, the prisoner was my washer-woman. I went to the watch-house; and they had just taken the prisoner in with the bundle; when I came in the watchhouse I knowed the prisoner and the bundle.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120219-16-person189">
                  RICHARD 
                  BEARD
               <interp inst="t18120219-16-person189" type="surname" value="BEARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120219-16-person189" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120219-16-person189" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. The prisoner, near twelve o'clock at night on the 20th of January, came to the watchhouse, she asked me to let her in, I did, she had a bundle, I saw there were three new calico shirts, and some half shirts in the bundle, she wanted to go out of the watchhouse again, I detained her; about half an hour after, the prosecutrix came to the watchhouse door, I told her we had a suspicious person there, she came in and claimed the shawl.</p>
               <p>Prosecutrix. These are all my things.</p>
               <p>The prisoner said nothing in her defence, nor called any witnesses to character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18120219-16-verdict95" type="verdictDescription">
